        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 1:57PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 157 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bamberg, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bamberg, Branchville, Bowman, Rowesville, Cope, and Bamberg County
Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
